donor_name: UNDP AS ADMINISTRATIVE AGENT FOR A JOINT PROGRAMME PASS THROUGH ARRANGEMENT
outputs.output_descr: The overall goal of the Joint Programme is to strengthen the national capacity in reducing child malnutrition and mortality particularly in the most vulnerable areas by introducing a multi-level approach that involves major stakeholders as well as communities. The programme is designed to complement ongoing effort to increase access to social services and infrastructre as a priority area of government policies including the Poverty Reduction Strategy and the National Health Development Plan (2008-2012).

project_descr: Promotion of Multi-Level Approach to Child Malnutrition
